type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I thInk those are compelling arguments. I have this working on my fork. I'll file a PR soon.","created_at":"2018-05-28T14:23:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-392540592","id":392540592,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5MjU0MDU5Mg==","updated_at":"2018-05-28T14:23:39.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/392540592","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Proposed API for object-space normal map support:\r\n```javascript\r\nmaterial.normalMap = myNormalMap;\r\nmaterial.objectSpaceNormalMap = true; \/\/ default false, implies a tangent-space normal map\r\n```\r\nOr\r\n```javascript\r\nmaterial.normalMap = myNormalMap;\r\nmaterial.normalMapType = THREE.ObjectSpaceNormalMapType; \/\/ default THREE.TangentSpaceNormalMapType\r\n```\r\nI prefer the second one, even though there are only two options in this case.\r\n\r\nOther options,\r\n```javascript\r\nmaterial.normalMapType = THREE.ObjectSpaceType; \/\/ default THREE.TangentSpaceType\r\n```\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nmaterial.normalMapType = THREE.ObjectSpaceNormalMap; \/\/ default THREE.TangentSpaceNormalMap\r\n```\r\n\r\n\/ping @mrdoob \r\n","created_at":"2018-06-04T05:36:00.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-394239162","id":394239162,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NDIzOTE2Mg==","updated_at":"2018-06-04T05:36:00.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/394239162","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Thanks for your propose.\r\nI prefer the second option because it allows multiple type supports.","created_at":"2018-06-04T10:14:49.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-394304729","id":394304729,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NDMwNDcyOQ==","updated_at":"2018-06-04T10:14:49.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/394304729","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/7882661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Julien-Arlandis","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc4ODI2NjE=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Julien-Arlandis","type":"User","id":7882661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley I think the names should be:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTHREE.ObjectSpace\r\nTHREE.TangentSpace\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe reason is that there are other spaces that could be useful for specification elsewhere and then we do not have to have duplicate constants.  Other spaces I can think of are:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTHREE.WorldSpace\r\nTHREE.ViewSpace \/ Camera but without perspective transform\r\nTHREE.LightSpace\r\nTHREE.ScreenSpace\r\nTHREE.CustomSpace \/ you specify a matrix that defines the space.\r\nTHREE.TextureSpace \/ a UV space.\r\n```\r\n\r\nMost of these spaces are basically just matrix selection, except for screen space which includes a perspective transform.  I do not think these should be implemented now, but if we follow this naming convention, we could.\r\n\r\nI think that having space specifiers is sort of cool.  I am sure there are at least a couple more than I am missing.","created_at":"2018-06-04T12:26:46.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-394336757","id":394336757,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NDMzNjc1Nw==","updated_at":"2018-06-04T12:26:46.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/394336757","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@bhouston \r\n\r\nTo clarify, I assume you are suggesting a different property name, too:\r\n```javascript\r\nmaterial.normalMap = myNormalMap;\r\nmaterial.normalMapSpace = THREE.ObjectSpace; \/\/ default THREE.TangentSpace\r\n```\r\n\r\n>I think that having space specifiers is sort of cool.\r\n\r\nI am not sure I see a use case for the others space types...","created_at":"2018-06-04T16:27:38.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-394416570","id":394416570,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NDQxNjU3MA==","updated_at":"2018-06-04T16:27:38.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/394416570","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@Ben-Mack Is there an public-domain model we can use in an example?","created_at":"2018-06-06T02:22:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-394919052","id":394919052,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NDkxOTA1Mg==","updated_at":"2018-06-06T02:22:39.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/394919052","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley I haven't found one, but you can generate it easily in xNormal by uncheck `Tangent space` in Normal map options","created_at":"2018-06-06T04:22:37.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-394935668","id":394935668,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NDkzNTY2OA==","updated_at":"2018-06-06T04:22:37.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/394935668","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6309393?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Ben-Mack","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYzMDkzOTM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Ben-Mack","type":"User","id":6309393,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Ben-Mack\/orgs"}},{"index":11,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> I am not sure I see a use case for the others space types...\r\n\r\nOften you want to apply a offset to an object and you want to specify in which space that offset is done: ViewSpace, ObjectSpace (local space) or WorldSpace.  Or if you want to rotate an object, you may want to specify the coordinate system.\r\n\r\nBasically these spaces can be used to show a transform widget in a specific coordinate system on an object and then you move it there.  There is already some of this in the ThreeJS editor as well as the Clara.io editor.  (In the ThreeJS editor remember there is a [ ] local check box that is switching between THREE.WorldSpace and THREE.ObjectSpace for the manipulators.)\r\n\r\nAlso I like being able to ask a node in the scene graph to give its its matrix in any of these spaces.  If you have this type of accessor on the scene graph, implementing manipulators that are flexible in which coordiante system they use becomes easy.\r\n\r\n```\r\nnode.getTransform( THREE.ViewSpace, camera );\r\nnode.getTransform( THREE.ObjectSpace );\r\nnode.getTransform( THREE.WorldSpace );\r\nnode.getTransform( THREE.CustomSpace, worldTransform );\r\nnode.getTransform( THREE.ParentSpace ); \/\/ the node above space.  Sometimes useful.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is a very useful generalization that other engines do.","created_at":"2018-06-06T12:17:28.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-395048055","id":395048055,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NTA0ODA1NQ==","updated_at":"2018-06-06T12:19:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/395048055","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":12,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@Ben-Mack can you create a simple example for @WestLangley ?  It would be helpful as you know how to use xNormal.","created_at":"2018-06-06T12:18:00.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139#issuecomment-395048182","id":395048182,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14139","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NTA0ODE4Mg==","updated_at":"2018-06-06T12:18